track_notes:
For those long distance walker SOTA activators out there. This was the route taken by G4OBK and M6PYG in May 2013 when we led a group of walkers over the Yorkshire 3 Peaks (age range 17-68). 
Pay Car Park in Horton - more info on the Yorkshire 3 Peaks website. 16 points available, 25 if you include the winter bonus.
The shortest way to the summit. There is limited roadside parking a few 100m in the direction of Ribblehead.
track_title: Ingleborough from the B6255 road Hill Inn

track_notes: The route starts from the Community Centre Car Park in the town (£4 per day). This is a more gradual ascent than from Hill Inn which may suit some people. The route is more enjoyable in my opinion. After the activation we walked down to Clapham via Little Ingleborough. You could then catch a bus (currently 1546pm back to the Ingleton Car Park. This would of course make this into a full day mission.
Route from lay by near Philpin Farm to Ingleborough summit

track_title: Ingleborough from Old Road near Newby
